OL,3,CWales is set to become a Bluetongue
OL,4,CRestricted Zone
OL,6,FTo date, eleven cases of BTV-3 have
OL,7,Fbeen confirmed in Wales, four in Powys
OL,8,Fand seven in the Temporary Control
OL,9,FZone located in Monmouthshire. The
OL,10,FWelsh Government says it is likely
OL,11,Fthat the number of Bluetongue cases
OL,12,Fwill increase as surveillance
OL,13,Fcontinues.
OL,15,FThe restricted zone relates to BTV-3
OL,16,Fonly. Controls may need to be
OL,17,Fintroduced for positive cases of new
OL,18,FBluetongue serotypes, should these
OL,19,Femerge in the future.
