OL,6,FHe added: "Vaccination remains the
OL,7,Fbest way to protect livestock and
OL,8,Flivelihoods from the worst impacts of
OL,9,FBluetongue, which can include both
OL,10,Fillness of affected livestock and
OL,11,Flonger-term effects on fertility and
OL,12,Fproductivity. It is more important
OL,13,Fthan ever to be prepared. With the
OL,14,Ffull support of industry, I strongly
OL,15,Fencourage animal keepers to discuss
OL,16,Fthe role and timing of Bluetongue
OL,17,Fvaccination of their herds and flocks
OL,18,Fwith their vets, particularly before
OL,19,Fthe next active transmission period
OL,20,Ffor the disease, in spring 2026."
